<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-08-04T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-08-04T16:00:00-05:00" n="679" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d679">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/2676: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-04T17:00:00-04:00">August 4, 1933—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>52. Your 82, and 83 and 84.<note n="62" xml:id="d679fn62">None
                                printed.</note> Certain difficulties of a legal nature have now been
                            raised regarding the Agreement for Financial Control <pb facs="0842" n="754" xml:id="pg_754"/> which require further consideration. Also
                            it appears advisable to await arrival of the Secretary the first of next
                            week. I greatly regret delay but will instruct you at the earliest
                            possible moment.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>